The paper discusses the evolution of co-authorship networks in scientific fields, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of scientometrics and social network analysis. The paper also uses a comprehensive dataset of scientific articles, which suggests a focus on data mining and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
